The paper deals with a problem in metric spaces and proposes competitive algorithms for it. This suggests that it could belong to categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of the polynomial method and the analysis of randomized algorithms suggest that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
